# Proton VPN — Linux Full System Setup

## Purpose

This script installs Proton VPN on Ubuntu/Debian-based systems, launches the GUI client, and prepares optional automation for repeated use.

All network traffic will route through the VPN once connected.

---

## Install Script

```bash
#!/bin/bash

set -e

echo "[+] Updating system..."
sudo apt update

echo "[+] Installing dependencies..."
sudo apt install -y wget apt-transport-https gnupg

echo "[+] Adding Proton repository..."
wget -qO - https://repo.protonvpn.com/debian/public_key.asc | \
gpg --dearmor | sudo tee /etc/apt/trusted.gpg.d/protonvpn.gpg > /dev/null

echo "deb https://repo.protonvpn.com/debian stable main" | \
sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/protonvpn.list

echo "[+] Installing Proton VPN..."
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y protonvpn-app

echo "[+] Installation complete."
echo "Run: protonvpn-app"
```

---

## Launch

```bash
protonvpn-app
```

Login using:

* Username: Proton email address
* Password: Proton account password

---

## Optional Quick Launcher

```bash
mkdir -p ~/bin
echo -e '#!/bin/bash\nprotonvpn-app' > ~/bin/vpn
chmod +x ~/bin/vpn
```

Then run:

```bash
vpn
```

---

## Verify Connection

```bash
curl ifconfig.me
```

If the IP is different from your ISP → VPN is active.

---

## Security Notes

* Enable Kill Switch inside the app.
* Enable Auto-connect on startup for persistent protection.
* Free tier has limited servers but full encryption.

---

## Reuse

This script can be copied to any compatible Linux system and reused.

Recommended filename:

```
install_protonvpn.sh
```
